      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That perspective reflects a growing consensus among energy experts who see nuclear as a necessary complement to intermittent renewables. The variable nature of wind and solar requires reliable, constant power sources to maintain grid stability when the sun isn't shining or the wind isn't blowing. However, advocates for renewables argue that advancements in battery storage and smart grid technology are rapidly closing the gap in reliability, making the necessity of nuclear less absolute.",
      "source": "target",
